12 - Generated JSON request decoders from Go API contracts:
- Keep JSON envelopes and Go structs as the source of truth.
- Extend `linuxio-api-gen` to emit backend request decoders plus frontend TS.
- Reject unknown fields, duplicate fields, missing required fields, and wrong scalar types.
- Do not hand-write per-route decoders; `make generate` should update them.
- Keep response encoding on `encoding/json` unless profiling proves it matters.
- See `docs/api-contract.md` Generated Request Decoder Plan.

13 - Docker update status persistence:
- Bridge-side reader/store is only half of the feature; the missing piece is the scheduled producer.
- Timer already starts `linuxio-watchtower.service`, but that service runs Watchtower directly and does not currently publish per-container JSON status.
- Preferred direction: ask upstream/fork Watchtower for stable JSON update-check report output (for example `--porcelain json` or `/v1/status`), then systemd can write/publish `/var/lib/linuxio/docker-update-status.json`.
- Avoid embedded shell parsers or bridge CLI commands for scheduled runs.
- Bridge should mostly read the JSON artifact and display update status.

14 - Filebrowser batch operations follow-ups (see docs/filebrowser-batch-operations.md):
- Batch uploads: copy/move/delete now run as one batch job, but upload is still one-job-per-file. Add a multi-file stream framing protocol so a folder uploads over a single job/stream (main remaining upgrade).
- Post-reload listing refresh: add batch (and pre-existing single) copy/move/delete job types to INVALIDATIONS_BY_JOB_TYPE so a job finishing after a page reload refreshes the listing.
- Remove dead single routes: filebrowser.copy/move/resource_delete + runCopyJob/runMoveJob/resourceDelete handlers + their recovery cases are no longer called by the frontend.
- Optional: auto-rename on collision for batch copy ("name (copy)") instead of skip-and-report, if best-effort behavior proves annoying.

